<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-09-28T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-09-28T15:00:00-05:00" n="623" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d623">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">501.BB/9–2848: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Embassy in the United
                                    Kingdom</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                                <lb/>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">us urgent</hi>
                            </seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-09-28T15:00:00-05:00">September
                                    28, 1948—3 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>3790. Louis [<hi rend="italic">Lewis</hi>] Jones from McClintock. Confirm
                            to Wright my remarks to him Sep 23 concerning desire Dept that, in light
                            existing circumstances, top priority be accorded treatment Palestine
                            problem Paris <gloss target="#t_GA1">GA</gloss>. [McClintock.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Lovett</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>